            <abstract>
                <p>The text of Vita of St Mercurius, <cit>
                        <quote>of which, for the moment, only the Geez version is known. It is an
                            abbreviated recension, made narratively consistent with the usual scheme
                            of the Gadl. </quote>
                    </cit> This text is classified in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/E7KSCCHW"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Proverbio1993PassioMercuri"/><title level="a">Le recensioni etiopiche della Passio Mercuri</title><title level="j">Studi Classici e Orientali</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Delio Vania</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Proverbio</t:surname></author><date>1993</date><biblScope unit="volume">43</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">453-466</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">459</citedRange></bibl>as 'recension c'. This text is known to be assigned for <date ref="ethiocal:Hedar25">25th of Ḫǝdār</date>.</p>
            </abstract>
